column2: The interest rate of the loan (more risky borrowers are assigned higher interest rates).
column3: The monthly installments owed by the borrower if the loan is funded.
column4: The FICO credit score of the borrower.
column5: The number of days the borrower has had a credit line.
column6: The borrower's number of inquiries by creditors in the last 6 months.
column7: The number of times the borrower had been 30+ days past due on a payment in the past 2 years.
column8: 1 if the loan is not fully paid
